<subSubSection id="C3776556EEAE3BCAFF78F966FD56F88B" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEAE3BCAFF78F966FD56F88B" blockId="511.[136,778,1397,2070]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFF78F966FEFBF903" bold="true" box="[189,318,1704,1730]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name is derived from the combination of 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFE85F904FEB7F922" box="[320,370,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">noto</emphasis>
(=”south” in Greek) and - 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFD6FF904FD13F922" box="[682,726,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">ixys</emphasis>
, the ending of several existing genera of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFD95F925FCC2F8C4" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[592,775,1771,1797]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodelphyidae</taxonomicName>
. The name alludes to the zoogeographic distribution of the new genus in the Antarctic or Southern Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EEAE3BCAFF78F89CFA5DF8C7" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEAE3BCAFF78F89CFB6BF961" blockId="511.[136,778,1397,2070]" lastBlockId="511.[810,1452,1397,1798]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFF78F89CFEEFF8AD" bold="true" box="[189,298,1874,1900]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFEF9F89CFE5BF8AA" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[316,414,1874,1899]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFEF9F89CFE5BF8AA" box="[316,414,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Notoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFE6DF89CFDD1F8AD" bold="true" box="[424,532,1874,1900]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEAE3BCAFE6DF89CFDD1F8AD" box="[424,532,1874,1900]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFF0DF8BAFEE8F84F" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[200,301,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFF0DF8BAFEE8F84F" box="[200,301,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Loboixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFEACF8BAFE0AF84C" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[361,463,1908,1933]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFEACF8BAFE0AF84C" box="[361,463,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more complex state of the armature on the oral appendages and swimming legs. Unlike the latter two genera, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFDCEF876FDA8F810" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[523,621,1976,2001]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFDCEF876FDA8F810" box="[523,621,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Notoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFDB1F876FD18F813" bold="true" box="[628,733,1976,2002]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEAE3BCAFDB1F876FD18F813" box="[628,733,1976,2002]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a 3-segmented endopod in the maxilla (cf. 2-segmented in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFF4DF832FF2BF7D4" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[136,238,2044,2069]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFF4DF832FF2BF7D4" box="[136,238,2044,2069]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 1- or 2-segmented in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFDC6F832FDADF7D7" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[515,616,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFDC6F832FDADF7D7" box="[515,616,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Loboixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and anarrow cutting edge on the coxal gnathobase in the mandible (vs. broad medial margin in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFB87FA56FB6DFA70" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[1090,1192,1432,1457]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFB87FA56FB6DFA70" box="[1090,1192,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFB21FA59FA8CFA70" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[1252,1353,1431,1457]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFB21FA59FA8CFA70" box="[1252,1353,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Loboixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFC7CFA77FBDBFA12" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[953,1054,1465,1491]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFC7CFA77FBDBFA12" box="[953,1054,1465,1491]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Loboixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having an inner seta on the first and second exopodal segments of legs 1 and 2, whereas setae on these segments are lacking in 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFB2BFA33FA9FF9D6" box="[1262,1370,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFB2BFA33FA92F9D6" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[1262,1367,1533,1559]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Loboixys</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
It also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFC00F9EEFBEEF9F8" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[965,1067,1568,1593]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFC00F9EEFBEEF9F8" box="[965,1067,1568,1593]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having an inner seta on the proximal segment(s) of endopods of legs 2–4 (vs. lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFC83F9AAFC69F9BC" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[838,940,1636,1661]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFC83F9AAFC69F9BC" box="[838,940,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and it lacks a tapering (exopodal) process on leg 5 which is present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFB87F948FB6DF95E" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[1090,1192,1670,1695]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFB87F948FB6DF95E" box="[1090,1192,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEAE3BCAFC9AF969FA5DF8C7" blockId="511.[810,1452,1397,1798]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">
The four species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFB90F966FB72F900" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1109,1207,1704,1729]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFB90F966FB72F900" box="[1109,1207,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Notoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFB01F966FAF6F903" bold="true" box="[1220,1331,1704,1730]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEAE3BCAFB01F966FAF6F903" box="[1220,1331,1704,1730]" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
described in the present work live in association with compound ascidians of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEAE3BCAFBE2F925FB4BF8C4" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1816" box="[1063,1166,1771,1797]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Polyclinidae" genus="Aplidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="511" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEAE3BCAFBE2F925FB4BF8C4" box="[1063,1166,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="511" pageNumber="512">Aplidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Antarctic Ocean.
</paragraph>
